Interface Detector

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MutantDetector

    public interface Detector
    The user of this interface has control to determinate if the ADN of a Subject is Human, Mutant or Alien.

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isMutant(java.lang.String[] dna)
      Determines from a given adn if the subject is human or mutant

    • Method Detail

      • isMutant

        boolean isMutant(java.lang.String[] dna)
          throws InputValidationException
        Determines from a given adn if the subject is human or mutant
        Parameters:
        dna - the sequence of adn to be evaluated to see if the subject is mutant or not
        Returns:
        True if the subject is mutant or False if its human
        Throws:
        InputValidationException - if the dna is alien
